                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/2674: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morales</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-08-30T09:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 30, 1923—9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 31—9:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>74. Referring to the Department’s telegram of August 28, 7 p.m. The President
                    informed me that he was willing to assure the candidates that he would not
                    impose a candidate at the forthcoming elections and would do everything within
                    his power to guarantee free elections. …</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
